# ========================================
TC-AMS-POSTSUBMIT-01

SUMMARY
AMS R1 Post-Submit - All AMS Notifications Responded To - Completed Tick and Message Displayed on Farmer Dashboard

DESCRIPTION
Verifies the Farmer Dashboard AMS Findings panel state after a farmer has submitted all their AMS responses in Round 1. Once all responses are submitted the panel must show a green tick with the label “All responses completed” instead of the red Response Required label. The notification count in the Amount column must remain unchanged. The panel must show a green “View Responses” button instead of the Respond to Findings button. If the farmer rejected any AMS notifications, a specific message must appear on the dashboard panel and also at the top of the AMS screen. If the farmer only accepted or withdrew notifications (no rejections), the message must NOT appear. This test covers both the reject and accept/withdraw message scenarios.

LABELS
AMS, FarmerDashboard, PostSubmit, Round1, TestOnly

COMPONENT
AMS - Farmer Dashboard - Post Submit Panel

ENVIRONMENT
CENTEST

ROUND
Round 1 - 2026

TEST DATA

Run on CENTEST_BISS_DATA - Find herd with AMS Round 1 findings that has already responded:
select LVL_HERD_NO, LML_PARCEL_LABEL, a.* from vwbs_ams_response a where lvl_year = 2026 and lvl_submit_id is not null and ams_round = 1 order by lvl_herd_no;

Run on CENTEST_BISS_INET - Get agent login for herd:
SELECT hbcus.bcus_bus_id AS HERDNO, (SELECT ui.uri_username FROM tdcr_user_info ui WHERE uri_ccs_bus_id = abcus.bcus_bus_id AND ROWNUM = 1) AS USERNAME FROM tdco_customer_asscs ca, tdco_business_customers abcus, tdco_business_customers hbcus WHERE SYSDATE BETWEEN ca.ca_start_date AND ca.ca_end_date AND ca.ca_cac_code = 194 AND ca.ca_bcus_id_from = abcus.bcus_id AND ca.ca_bcus_id_to = hbcus.bcus_id AND hbcus.bcus_bus_id = ‘<HERD_NUMBER>’ ORDER BY ca.ca_start_date DESC;

PRECONDITIONS

- Herd has Red AMS findings in Round 1
- Farmer has already submitted ALL AMS responses (all parcels responded to)
- At least one response must be a Rejection for the message sub-scenario
- A second herd where all responses are Accept or Withdraw only (no rejection) is needed for the no-message sub-scenario

STEPS

Action	Data	Expected Result
Log in to BISS as farmer or agent with credentials and OTP	Agent username and password. OTP/PIN	Successfully authenticated and landed on BISS Home page
Navigate to Farmer Dashboard for herd that has submitted all AMS responses	Herd number from vwbs_ams_response query where lvl_submit_id IS NOT NULL	Farmer Dashboard displayed
Locate AMS Findings panel on dashboard		Panel is visible on Farmer Dashboard
Verify panel header	 	Header reads exactly “AMS findings”
Verify AMS status section below header		AMS status section displayed underneath header
Verify red triangle icon and label		Red triangle symbol visible with label “AMS findings”
Verify the Response Required label is GONE and replaced with completed label		Label reads “All responses completed” with a green tick to the right — NOT “Response required” with red symbol
Verify the Amount column notification count		Count of notifications remains the same as before submission — count is unchanged
Verify the View Responses button is present		Green “View Responses” button is visible — NOT “Respond to findings” button
Verify the Respond to findings button is ABSENT		“Respond to findings” button is NOT visible
Sub-scenario A - Verify dashboard message when farmer HAS rejected at least one notification		Message displayed on AMS panel on Farmer Dashboard: “You have submitted your AMS responses, please respond to any AgriSnap requests promptly”
Sub-scenario B - Verify NO message when farmer has ONLY accepted or withdrawn notifications (no rejections)		Message “You have submitted your AMS responses, please respond to any AgriSnap requests promptly” is NOT displayed on the panel
Click View Responses button		Navigated to the AMS screen
Verify AMS screen displays parcels and responses		All parcels and their submitted responses are visible on the AMS screen
Verify the side drawer is NOT shown		Side drawer does not open — no editing interface visible
Verify the Submit button is ABSENT on the AMS screen		Submit button is NOT visible post-submission
Verify Back button is present		Back button is visible on the AMS screen
Verify pagination is present if more than one page of parcels		Pagination controls visible if parcel count requires multiple pages
Sub-scenario A - Verify blue message at top of AMS screen when farmer HAS rejected at least one notification		Blue message displayed at top of AMS screen: “You have submitted your AMS responses, please respond to any AgriSnap requests promptly”
Sub-scenario B - Verify NO blue message at top of AMS screen when farmer has ONLY accepted or withdrawn		Blue message is NOT displayed at top of AMS screen

# ========================================
TC-AMS-POSTSUBMIT-02

SUMMARY
AMS R1 Post-Submit - View Responses Button Opens AMS Screen in Read Only Mode

DESCRIPTION
Verifies that after a farmer has submitted all AMS Round 1 responses, clicking the green View Responses button on the Farmer Dashboard AMS panel correctly navigates to the AMS screen where all parcels and responses are displayed in read-only mode. No editing must be possible post-submission. The side drawer must not be shown when a parcel row is clicked or viewed. The Submit button must be absent. The Back button and pagination (if applicable) must be present. This test focuses specifically on the read-only behaviour of the AMS screen post-submit.

LABELS
AMS, FarmerDashboard, PostSubmit, ReadOnly, Round1, TestOnly

COMPONENT
AMS - Respond to Findings - Post Submit Read Only

ENVIRONMENT
CENTEST

ROUND
Round 1 - 2026

TEST DATA

Run on CENTEST_BISS_DATA - Find herd with all AMS responses submitted:
select LVL_HERD_NO, LML_PARCEL_LABEL, a.* from vwbs_ams_response a where lvl_year = 2026 and lvl_submit_id is not null and ams_round = 1 order by lvl_herd_no;

Run on CENTEST_BISS_INET - Get agent login for herd:
SELECT hbcus.bcus_bus_id AS HERDNO, (SELECT ui.uri_username FROM tdcr_user_info ui WHERE uri_ccs_bus_id = abcus.bcus_bus_id AND ROWNUM = 1) AS USERNAME FROM tdco_customer_asscs ca, tdco_business_customers abcus, tdco_business_customers hbcus WHERE SYSDATE BETWEEN ca.ca_start_date AND ca.ca_end_date AND ca.ca_cac_code = 194 AND ca.ca_bcus_id_from = abcus.bcus_id AND ca.ca_bcus_id_to = hbcus.bcus_id AND hbcus.bcus_bus_id = ‘<HERD_NUMBER>’ ORDER BY ca.ca_start_date DESC;

PRECONDITIONS

- Herd has Red AMS findings in Round 1
- Farmer has already submitted ALL AMS responses
- Agent login resolved via INET query

STEPS

Action	Data	Expected Result
Log in to BISS as farmer or agent with credentials and OTP	Agent username and password. OTP/PIN	Successfully authenticated and landed on BISS Home page
Navigate to Farmer Dashboard for herd with all AMS responses submitted	Herd number from vwbs_ams_response query	Farmer Dashboard displayed
Locate AMS Findings panel on dashboard		Panel is visible on Farmer Dashboard
Verify panel header		Header reads exactly “AMS findings”
Verify AMS status section below header		AMS status section displayed underneath header
Verify red triangle icon and label		Red triangle symbol visible with label “AMS findings”
Verify All responses completed label with green tick		Label reads “All responses completed” with green tick to the right
Verify the Amount column notification count is unchanged		Count of notifications is the same as before submission
Verify View Responses button is present		Green “View Responses” button is visible
Click View Responses button		Navigated to the AMS screen
Verify all parcels are displayed on the AMS screen		All parcels with their submitted responses are visible
Verify responses are displayed for each parcel		Each parcel row shows the response that was submitted - Accept, Reject, or Withdraw
Verify the AMS screen is read only - attempt to click a parcel row		Side drawer does NOT open - no editing interface displayed
Verify no input fields or dropdowns are editable on the AMS screen		All fields are read only - no Accept/Reject dropdown, no reason selection visible
Verify the Submit button is ABSENT		Submit button is NOT visible anywhere on the AMS screen
Verify the Back button is present		Back button visible on the AMS screen
Verify pagination if parcel count exceeds one page		Pagination controls displayed if multiple pages of parcels exist
Click Back button		Navigated back to Farmer Dashboard